# **Intuition**
You need to know how to count the the number of islands
Refer to [200. Number of Islands](https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-islands/discuss/1284203/C%2B%2BPython-DFS-Solution)
<br>

# **Explanation**
Based on solution above,
return 0 if and only if we find it's not a sub island.
<br>

# **Complexity**
Time `O(mn)`
Space `O(mn)`
<br>

**Java**
```java
    public int countSubIslands(int[][] B, int[][] A) {
        int m = A.length, n = A[0].length, res = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++)
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
                if (A[i][j] == 1)
                    res += dfs(B, A, i, j);
        return res;
    }


    private int dfs(int[][] B, int[][] A, int i, int j) {
        int m = A.length, n = A[0].length, res = 1;
        if (i < 0 || i == m || j < 0 || j == n || A[i][j] == 0) return 1;
        A[i][j] = 0;
        res &= dfs(B, A, i - 1, j);
        res &= dfs(B, A, i + 1, j);
        res &= dfs(B, A, i, j - 1);
        res &= dfs(B, A, i, j + 1);
        return res & B[i][j];
    }
```

