solutions.content:
A valid island contains land cells in both grids, and it is not connected to any new land cell in grid2. Based on this, we can do a preprocessing: `gird1 = gird1 * 2 - grid2` to get the difference of two grids. We would get `-1`, `0`, `1` and `2` in the difference grid:
- `grid[i][j] == -1`: `(i, j)` is water in grid1 and land in grid2
- `grid[i][j] == 0`: `(i, j)` is water in grid1 and water in grid2
- `grid[i][j] == 1`: `(i, j)` is land in grid1 and land in grid2
- `grid[i][j] == 2`: `(i, j)` is land in grid1 and water in grid2

By doing this, we can simply search for cells with value `1` in the difference grid (i.g. `grid1`), and check if it is connected to any cells with value `-1`, if yes then this island is invalid and should not be counted as subisland; otherwise it's valid and we should increment `count`.

```java
class Solution {
    public int countSubIslands(int[][] grid1, int[][] grid2) {
        // preprocess two grids:
        // gird1 = gird1 * 2 - grid2
        for (int i = 0; i < grid1.length; ++i) {
            for (int j = 0; j < grid1[0].length; ++j) {
                grid1[i][j] = grid1[i][j] * 2 - grid2[i][j];
            }
        }

        // count valid islands
        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < grid1.length; ++i) {
            for (int j = 0; j < grid1[0].length; ++j) {
                if (grid1[i][j] == 1 && isValid(grid1, i, j)) {
                    count++;
                }
            }
        }
        return count;
    }

    private boolean isValid(int[][] grid, int r, int c) {
        // if the index is invalid, simply return true and end this recursion
        if (r < 0 || c < 0 || r >= grid.length || c >= grid[0].length) {
            return true;
        }

        // grid[r][c] == 2: this cell is land in grid1 but is water in grid2
        // grid[r][c] == 0: this cell is land in both grid1 and grid2
        if (grid[r][c] == 2 || grid[r][c] == 0) return true;

        // grid[r][c] == -1: this cell is water in grid1 but is land in grid2
        if (grid[r][c] == -1) return false;

        // mark this cell as visited
        grid[r][c] = 0;

        return isValid(grid, r-1, c) & isValid(grid, r+1, c) & isValid(grid, r, c+1) & isValid(grid, r, c-1);

    }
}
```

