solutions.content:
*Key Point here is,
we do not return instantly if we found a false as answer
but instead we are going to traverse the whole portion
so that the remaining part will not make any difficulty in future.*

**This is how we are going to make tree.**
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/ed2487ec-69d4-4da7-9bcf-86a0a71aef3c_1625763540.6736279.jpeg)

**Code**
## Java
```
class Solution {
    int[][] dir = {{1, 0}, {0, 1}, {-1, 0}, {0, -1}};
    int n, m;
    private boolean dfs(int[][] grid1, int[][] grid2, int i, int j) {
        grid2[i][j] = 0;
        boolean res = true;
        for (int d = 0; d < dir.length; ++d) {
            int r = i + dir[d][0];
            int c = j + dir[d][1];
            if (r >= 0 && c >= 0 && r < n && c < m && grid2[r][c] == 1) {
                res = dfs(grid1, grid2, r, c) && res;
				/*
				This is the portion where we are applying the key point
				we putted res, after the dfs call,
				so that it will traverse the whole island and convert it to sea
				and after that only it will return false/true as answer.
				*/
            }
        }
        return res && grid1[i][j] == 1;
    }
    public int countSubIslands(int[][] grid1, int[][] grid2) {
        n = grid1.length;
        m = grid1[0].length;
        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
            for (int j = 0; j < m ; ++j)
                if (grid2[i][j] == 1)
                    count += dfs(grid1, grid2, i, j) ? 1 : 0;
        return count;
    }
}
