Solution 1: I started with a brute force solution in which I first performed dfs on Grid1 and from that I marked all corresponding cells in Grid2 with value 1 to value 2. Then, another DFS on Grid2 in which values should be only contains 2s and no 1s. It gave Timeout
Solution 2: Then, as a improvement, I applied memoization on Grid2. It passed with acceptance%- 10%.
Solution 3: Then, as a improvement, I found that the first DFS can be eliminated by checking Grid1 from Grid2. Before I was checking Grid2 from Grid1. Passed at acceptance-  >90%.

```
from functools import lru_cache

class Solution:
    def countSubIslands(self, grid1: List[List[int]], grid2: List[List[int]]) -> int:
        visited=set()
        n=len(grid1)
        m=len(grid1[0])

        @lru_cache(None)
        def find_subisland(i,j):
            if(i<0 or j<0 or i==n or j==m or grid2[i][j]==0):
                return True
            if(grid1[i][j]==0):
                return False
            if((i,j) in visited):
                return True
            visited.add((i,j))

            return find_subisland(i+1,j) and find_subisland(i-1,j) and find_subisland(i,j-1) and find_subisland(i,j+1)

        visited=set()
        ans=0
        for i in range(n):
            for j in range(m):
                if(grid2[i][j]==1 and (i,j) not in visited):
                    if(find_subisland(i,j)):
                        ans+=1
        return ans

