Create method traverseIsland that will return true if that island is a subIsland of grid1 or else false.
Algorithm
1. If we get out of index or cell is already visited and its not possible to go further return true, this will terminate the function. 
2.  Lets say this element which we are on is not a part of any island in grid1 we return false as per our method definition.
3.  We traverse in all four directions and we see if we can traverse there or not, if the next cell is part of island in grid2 and is not part of island in grid1 false will be returned giving the conclusion that this island is not the right island and should not be included in our ans.

