Okay, so this problem is very very similar to counting the number of islands in a matrix.
Here while we are in the dfs function to mark all the current island indexes as 0, if there exists any index in grid1 that has water but we have land on that place in grid2, then this means it is not a valid sub island. So, we will mark the current island as false, and thus does not increase our final count.
If otherwise, we increase the count.
