solutions.content:
The solution is just basic dfs on 2d grid twice
1. First go through the first grid and check if there is any 0(water) for which there is 1(land) in grid 2
      If yes make all such land in grid 2 as visited.
2. Second just traverse through the grid 2 and count the no of connected components.
This is the basic intuition. 
